&lt;p&gt;Yes, totally agree. Actually this bug was introduced by a small change in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8726&quot; title=&quot;The Secrets in Credentials are not available to MR tasks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-8726&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-8726&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (see the change between &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12542820/HADOOP-8726.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12542820/HADOOP-8726.patch&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12542928/HADOOP-8726.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12542928/HADOOP-8726.patch&lt;/a&gt;).  We should be more careful when checking in small changes in the future.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13965807" author="daryn" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 20:32:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this patch fixes the problem.  The ArrayList constructor is also iterating over the values in the token map to make a copy, so it too can encounter the CME.  The race is now smaller but the problem remains.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13965824" author="jingzhao" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 20:46:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From the UGI point of view, getTokens and addToken are both protected by the UGI&apos;s monitor, thus can protect the race in UGI?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13965851" author="daryn" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 21:02:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, UGI synchronization is not trustworthy.   Calling &lt;tt&gt;UGI.getCurrentUser()&lt;/tt&gt; twice will return you two distinct objects which means synchronization is often worthless.  I&apos;ve contemplated multiple ways to fix this but haven&apos;t had time to devote to the task.  In the scope of this jira, you may want to synch on the Subject which is indeed shared between UGI instances.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13965859" author="jingzhao" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 21:14:18 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Calling UGI.getCurrentUser() twice will return you two distinct objects which means synchronization is often worthless&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hmm, you&apos;re right. I will create a separate jira to track this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13965870" author="jingzhao" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 21:25:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-10489&quot; title=&quot;UserGroupInformation#getTokens and UserGroupInformation#addToken can lead to ConcurrentModificationException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-10489&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-10489&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Thanks for pointing out the issue, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daryn&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daryn&quot;&gt;daryn&lt;/a&gt;! Please feel free to assign that jira to yourself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
